# Files aider MUST NOT modify when editing pxx itself. Mirrors the
# "Hard guardrails" list in CLAUDE.md — wrong values OOM the Studio, break
# installs, or alter agent behavior subtly. Edit these by hand only.

# Ollama context windows / call parameters — wrong values can OOM the Studio
config/model-settings.yml

# Aider's own defaults — change behavior in subtle ways
config/aider.conf.yml
.aider.conf.yml

# Package metadata + dependencies — break installs
pyproject.toml

# Meta — the guardrails themselves
.aiderignore
CONVENTIONS.md

# Optimizer-protected: the candidate generator must never edit its own gates,
# evaluator, or hidden checks (docs/TRUST_BOUNDARY.md). The loop's scope gate
# is the primary boundary; this is the editor-level backstop the trust
# boundary claims. Precise per-file (not blanket tests/) so the loop can still
# do legitimate test work elsewhere.
pxx/safety.py
pxx/scope.py
pxx/governance.py
pxx/review_gate.py
pxx/loop.py
pxx/evaluation.py
pxx/calibration.py
pxx/promotion.py
pxx/candidates.py
pxx/candidate_eval.py
pxx/content_candidates.py
pxx/improvement.py
pxx/protected_paths.py
evals/
.github/workflows/
tests/test_safety.py
tests/test_scope.py
tests/test_governance.py
tests/test_review_gate.py
tests/test_loop.py
tests/test_evaluation.py
tests/test_calibration.py
tests/test_promotion.py
tests/test_candidates.py
tests/test_outcomes.py
tests/test_improvement.py
tests/test_workflow_contract.py
